      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 36
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_8_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_8",
      "description": "Available is a concours-level 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, an analog masterpiece of 50:50 weight distribution and lightweight engineering. This example retains its numbers-matching 13B-REW twin-rotor engine, producing exceptional compression numbers documented via recent bench testing. The sequential twin-turbocharger system operates flawlessly, providing a seamless transition from the primary to secondary turbine. Power is delivered through a precise five-speed manual gearbox to a factory Torsen limited-slip differential. The chassis is free of oxidation, featuring original double-wishbone suspension and 4-piston aluminum calipers. Inside, the cockpit is immaculate, with no sun-fading on the plastics or bolster fatigue on the seats. A rare opportunity for the collector seeking mechanical absolute purity.",
      "price": 48500.0,
      "reputation": 0.6,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 36
    },
    {
